                            <comment id="69238" author="cbeams" created="Thu, 11 Aug 2011 11:06:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report - we&apos;ll see what we can improve here during 3.2, when we plan to make a number of other related improvements.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86016" author="cbeams" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 04:32:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bozhidar, thanks again for bringing this up. An update:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve since eliminated the containers/servers field entirely. It was very infrequently used anyway, and folks can just mention what platform they&apos;re on in the description or comments as necessary.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We won&apos;t add &quot;BUILD-SNAPSHOT&quot; versions into the affects version; it&apos;s a bit of a hassle to manage doing so, and it&apos;s not necessarily helpful - assuming we don&apos;t get to the issue right away, the question would quickly become &quot;exactly which &lt;b&gt;number&lt;/b&gt; of BUILD-SNAPSHOT were you running&quot;, which can&apos;t be managed via the drop-down anyway. In your case above, marking M2 as the affects version and then just mentioning that you&apos;re actually tracking the latest snapshot is fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tmarshall&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tmarshall&quot;&gt;Trevor Marshall&lt;/a&gt;, I&apos;m assigning this to you for the moment - could you review our current permission scheme and what&apos;s possible in JIRA overall to see if we can get to the point where reporters can edit their own descriptions and commenters can edit their own comments? Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86092" author="tmarshall" created="Thu, 13 Dec 2012 10:21:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It was already the case that the Users role (in this case, any logged in user) could edit their own comments.. that might have been updated since this issue was logged.&lt;br/&gt;
Reporters are now able to edit their own issues.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cbeams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cbeams&quot;&gt;Chris Beams&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86094" author="cbeams" created="Thu, 13 Dec 2012 10:32:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Trevor!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
